Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Hand MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Impaction and Impingement Syndrome' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Ulnocarpal impaction syndrome' radio button is enabled
And 'Radioulnar impingement' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Ulnocarpal impaction syndrome' radio button
Then 'Articular cartilage damage' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased subchondral sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cyst formation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema' checkbox is enabled

And 'Ulna' checkbox is enabled
And 'Os lunatum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Os triquetrum' checkbox is enabled
And 'TFCC' checkbox is enabled

And 'Positive ulnar variance' radio button is enabled
And 'Status post radius fracture with positive ulnar variance' radio button is enabled
And 'Lunate necrosis' checkbox is enabled
